parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brakes lock up
the vehicle slides or skids while braking
the ABS system malfunctions
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out brake pads and rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or bounce while braking, leading to reduced stopping power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or bounces while braking
the brake pads are worn out
the rotors are warped or out of round.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the brake bearings can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake bearings are corroded
the brakes fail to respond to pedal application.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Master Cylinder Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the brake pedal and master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the master cylinder is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can cause the vehicle to pull to one side while braking, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes fail to respond to pedal application intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle speed control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the throttle gets stuck
the brakes fail to slow the vehicle down
the cruise control switch ignites
and the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and can also pose a risk to the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the hood
flames appearing from the engine compartment
burning plastic
and a strong burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to significant damage and potentially posing a risk to the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The cruise control switch ignites
smoke comes from the engine compartment
and the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle loses braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering or implosion of the rear window can cause a loud noise, propel glass shards into the passenger compartment, and potentially distract the driver, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear window shatters or implodes
often with a loud noise
while the rear defroster is in use or without any apparent reason
resulting in glass fragments scattered throughout the vehicle.
